about:
T.C.A.R. is a non-profit, no-kill rescue organization located in Vancouver, WA. We provide temporary shelter and medical care for abandoned, abused, neglected, orphaned and special needs animals until they are adopted into a loving permanent homes through our adoption program.  
Our mission is to reduce the number of adoptable animals euthanized in overcrowded shelters and when possiable those running at large. Restore them to good health and through adoption, provide them permanent loving homes. 
We accomplish our mission by:
- rescuing cats/kittens, dogs/puppies, rodents, birds and some reptiles: 
- Providing spay or neuter surgeries prior to adoption;
- providing rehabilitative medical care;
- providing vaccinations, flea and deworming treatments to animals in our care;
- providing low cost microchips;
- providing food, medicines, supplies;
- providing community education;
- providing safe loving foster homes;
- facilitating successful adoptions; and
- ensuring no adoptable animal in our care is euthanized

