about:
The Calhoun County Humane Society, Inc. (dba The Animal Shelter), located in Anniston, Alabama, was established in 1973 as a result of the efforts of Susan Levens Phillips. 

Our mission is 

**To provide the pets in our care with a decent, safe and sanitary place;
**To prevent cruelty to animals;
**To stop suffering among animals mutilated or injured;
**To educate the public about the tremendous pet over-population facing the United States;
**To promote spaying and neutering to stop the senseless killing of animals;
**To place as many pets as possible in responsible homes.

The Mission of All American Dachshund Rescue is to Protect the Welfare of Dachshunds, to Promote the Humane Treatment and Well Being of these Animals by:

o Providing shelter and medical care for stray and abandoned Dachshunds;
o Responding with personal commitment, humane sensitivity, compassion, and technical skill to the needs of these Dachshunds;
o Actively promoting suitable adoptions of Dachshunds;
o Encouraging spaying and neutering to ensure the numbers of unwanted Dachshunds be kept to a minimum;
o Helping to prevent cruelty to animals by promoting animal welfare education
